<!-- CycloneDDS configuration for Go2 EDU communication over dedicated ethernet.

     SINGLE robot-facing interface ONLY. This matches the official Unitree
     unitree_ros2/setup.sh verbatim (single <NetworkInterface name="enpXXX"
     multicast="default"/>, NO lo, NO Peers, NO ParticipantIndex) and two
     known-good community Go2 stacks (autonomy_stack_go2, go2_rl_ws), all of
     which run full multi-node stacks SAME-HOST on a single enx interface.

     HISTORY: a prior config (commit 72dfabb) added a second `lo` interface +
     a localhost <Peer> to "fix same-host discovery". Deep research (2026-06-16,
     3-0 verified vs official setup.sh) found that multi-homed lo+enx binding is
     the ROOT CAUSE of the Go2 never being discovered (0 subs on
     /api/sport/request, `ddsi_udp_conn_write ... retcode -3` when a Go2 unicast
     peer was added). Single-enx is the fix. The original same-host diagnosis was
     made with a fake subscriber + the `ros2` CLI that hangs under cyclonedds
     regardless — not a valid test. Verify same-host with demo talker/listener.

     Modern <Interfaces> syntax: the deprecated <NetworkInterfaceAddress> element
     silently breaks interface/multicast binding on newer CycloneDDS.

     name= is the onboard NIC on the Go2 (192.168.123.x) subnet. Default eno1
     (proven topology, this Jetson). Do NOT use the USB-eth adapter enx<mac>: it
     delivers 0 inbound multicast, so the Go2 is never discovered — see
     docs/go2-drive-activation-design.md. Verify with: ip a

     STAGED FALLBACK (only if single-enx multicast does not discover the Go2,
     and ONLY after confirming same-host talker/listener works):
       1. multicast group-join on a USB-eth adapter can fail even though tcpdump
          sees the Go2 SPDP multicast (tcpdump does not join the IGMP group).
       2. If so, add unicast discovery WITHOUT re-adding lo:
            <Discovery><Peers><Peer address="192.168.123.161"/></Peers></Discovery>
          (AllowMulticast=spdp will NOT help — spdp still discovers via multicast.)
       Re-test reading /sportmodestate before any motion. -->
<CycloneDDS>
  <Domain Id="any">
    <General>
      <Interfaces>
        <NetworkInterface name="eno1" priority="default" multicast="default" />
      </Interfaces>
    </General>
  </Domain>
</CycloneDDS>
